======= bitmap-lib ========
=====  documentation ======


---- data types and structures ----
- color_t
  A 32-bit value that stores a 24-bit RGB color code (first
  8 bits are ignored)

- bmp_t,
  Holds basic info about a .bmp file (width, height and pixel array)


---- macros ----

RGB(r, g, b) -> returns the color_t value of an (r, g, b) value.
                r, g and b are between 0 and 255 (0x00 and 0xFF).
                
RGB32(r, g, b) -> same as RGB(r, g, b)


---- functions ----

bmp_t   bmp_create(size_t width, size_t height);
    Create and initialize a bmp_t structure based on the
    width and the height of the desired .bmp file.


bmp_t   bmp_load(const char *filename);
    Load a .bmp image from a certain file and return
    the correspondent bmp_t structure.


void    bmp_free(bmp_t bmp);
    Free memory resources associated to a bmp_t structure.
    Use it when finishing your programs.


void    bmp_write(bmp_t bmp, const char *filename);
    Save a bmp_t structure that resides in memory as a
    new .bmp file.

void    bmp_dwrite(bmp_t bmp, int fd);
    Same as bmp_write, but writing it directly to a certain
    file descriptor.


void    bmp_set_pixel(bmp_t bmp, size_t x, size_t y, uint32_t color);
    Set value for a certain (x, y) pixel in the bmp_t image.
    A bmp_write() is needed to save the changes in the file.


color_t bmp_get_pixel(bmp_t bmp, size_t x, size_t y);
    get the color value for a certain (x, y) pixel in
    the bmp_t image.
